        <notes><![CDATA[
   file name: log4j-api-2.22.1.jar
   CVE-2025-68161 affects log4j-core's Socket Appender (TLS hostname verification), not log4j-api.
   The plugin does not bundle log4j-core - it is provided by Elasticsearch at runtime.
   log4j-api:2.22.1 is a transitive dependency from log4j-api-scala_3:13.1.0.
   The actual vulnerability exists in Elasticsearch's log4j-core (version 2.19.0), which the plugin cannot fix.
   Upgrading log4j-api to 2.25.3 without matching log4j-core causes runtime compatibility issues.
   This must be fixed by Elasticsearch upgrading to log4j-core:2.25.3+.
   ]]></notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.apache\.logging\.log4j/log4j-api@2\.22\.1.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2025-68161</cve>
    </suppress>
